 {\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetBody(s.author, body))\n\t}\n\tif err := e.Commit(s.repo); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\treturn e.Id(), nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3b: Add `SetContentType`**\n\nIn `internal/store/store.go`, after `SetKind` (mirror it exactly):\n\n```go\n// SetContentType replaces an entry's content type.\nfunc (s *Store) SetContentType(id entity.Id, contentType string) error {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetContentType(s.author, contentType))\n\t\treturn e.Commit(s.repo)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/store/...`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/store/\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): AddWithContentType and SetContentType\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: `render` body rendering (glamour + chroma)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go` (add `ShowOptions`, `ShowHeader`, `RenderBody`; rework `Show`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go:732-739` (update the one `render.Show` call site to the new signature â€” done fully in Task 7; here just keep the build green)\n- Test: `internal/render/render_test.go`\n- Add deps: glamour, chroma\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add the dependencies**\n\nRun:\n```bash\ngo get github.com/charmbracelet/glamour@latest\ngo get github.com/alecthomas/chroma/v2@latest\ngo mod tidy\n```\nExpected: `go.mod`/`go.sum` updated. (bubbletea/bubbles are added in Task 8.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing test**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"RenderBody\", func() {\n\tIt(\"renders markdown headings as text (no raw '#') in plain mode\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.RenderBody(\u0026b, \"# Title\\n\\